The most recent version of protoc (`libprotoc 35.0`) has some issues with PHP formatting:

```
$ protoc --version
libprotoc 35.0
```

1. Constructor uses uppercase `NULL` instead of lowercase `null`. This is ONLY in the constructor, and nowhere else in the gencode. [Here](https://github.com/googleapis/google-cloud-php/blob/5a95b9e9858c143edf3503f4b33949a6bc09221e/SecretManager/src/V1/Secret.php#L231) is an example:
```diff
-    public function __construct($data = NULL) {
+    public function __construct($data = null) {
```

2. Additionally, the opening curly braces are "cuddly", but this is not idomatic either. In all other functions the curly braces are on a newline:
```diff
-    public function __construct($data = NULL) {
+    public function __construct($data = NULL)
+    {
```

3. For unwrapped setters, the closing curly brace is missing a newline. [Here](https://github.com/googleapis/google-cloud-php/blob/5a95b9e9858c143edf3503f4b33949a6bc09221e/CommonProtos/src/Api/Service.php#L1236-L1239) is an example:

```diff
    public function setConfigVersionUnwrapped($var)
    {
        $this->writeWrapperValue("config_version", $var);
-       return $this;}
+       return $this;
+   }
```

 4. The access of oneofs uses double quotes instead of single quotes

```diff
    public function setConfigVersionUnwrapped($var)
    {
-       $this->writeWrapperValue("config_version", $var);
+       $this->writeWrapperValue('config_version', $var);
        return $this;}
    }
```
